<h3>The Many Genres</h3>
<p>
Sid and Roy’s discography ran the gamut of genres, sung by a vast constellation of stars. They were equally at home
with love songs, children’s songs, and just plain fun songs. As <cite>The New York Times</cite> put it, their songs
were characterized by an unbeatable combination of catchy melody and clever lyrics. With over 300 published songs, they
covered many genres, not by design, but simply because that’s where the spirit took them.
</p>
