<h4>Movie Songs</h4>

<p>
  Most notable, of course, is the fact that Sid and Roy played a significant role in the Elvis firmament, having had 42
  songs recorded by “the King”. They were one of the few go-to teams when Elvis needed romantic or witty songs in his
  films that were amenable to his own special sauce that would resonate with his fans. In addition to the title songs of
  two Elvis movies &mdash;
  <%= external_link('“GI Blues”', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GkyjCJvHLsA') %>
  and
  <%= external_link('“Stay Away”', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J_wD4o3pqq8') %>
  &mdash; Sid and Roy penned the title songs to Cliff Richard’s
  <%= external_link('“The Young Ones”', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BxNohANhJiA') %>
  and Donald O’Connor’s
  <%= external_link('“Francis, the Talking Mule”  ', 'https://youtu.be/p82-fgTZpLI') %>
  .
</p>
